perl-IPC-Run3: perl-IPC-Run3 (run a subprocess with input/ouput redirection)
perl-IPC-Run3:
perl-IPC-Run3: IPC-Run3 module allows you to run a subprocess and redirect stdin,
perl-IPC-Run3: stdout, and/or stderr to files and perl data structures.  It aims to
perl-IPC-Run3: satisfy 99% of the need for using system, qx, and open3 with a
perl-IPC-Run3: simple, extremely Perlish API and none of the bloat and rarely used
perl-IPC-Run3: features of IPC::Run.
